Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.27,0:00:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From a different perspective...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.77,0:00:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An imposing wall is just a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.56,0:00:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A text message that resembles a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as Uncle Kogorou is stumped,\Nit's a kitty to the rescue!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.78,0:00:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.11,0:00:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, meet with the client at 9:00 AM...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.23,0:01:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from 10:00 AM to 1:00 PM, eat lunch at Poirot and enjoy a relaxing coffee time...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.15,0:01:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from 2:00 PM, watch Okino Yoko-chan's soap opera that I've been waiting for so long while videotaping it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.61,0:02:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At which point I thoroughly theorize on future developments...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.58,0:02:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.99,0:02:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should skim through the previous five episodes before the client comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.83,0:02:10.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not bad a plan since I can review the storyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.88,0:02:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, I'm so busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.96,0:02:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Living my life to the fullest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.26,0:02:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.22,0:02:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it already time to go to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.31,0:02:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.64,0:02:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.64,0:02:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you hiding from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not anything weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the, it's just a cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.08,0:02:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.08,0:02:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.04,0:02:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.13,0:03:01.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,THE SECRET OF THE RUSSIAN BLUE
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you pick it up off the streets?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.06,0:03:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.89,0:03:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Aunt Eri's cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.35,0:03:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought her cat was brown-colored with black spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.94,0:03:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not this weird grayish color like a rat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This cat is called a Russian Blue, which has blue-gray fur and green eyes as unique characteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.24,0:03:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said that her old cat died last month, and she got this one from a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It died of old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, why is this freaking cat in my agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.96,0:03:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Mom just dropped by earlier and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.59,0:03:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.26,0:03:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gan you watch this cat for three days?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.76,0:03:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.06,0:03:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to take the afternoon flight to Okinawa where my client awaits...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.60,0:03:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kuriyama-san who was supposed to take care of this kid is bedridden with the flu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:03:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.32,0:04:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have anyone else to turn to except you, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.28,0:04:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.82,0:04:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take care of Goro-chan then, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.66,0:04:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:13.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch the cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when you guys go to school, I'm the one who's gotta take care of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.92,0:04:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.26,0:04:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.47,0:04:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're gonna be late, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.01,0:04:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I interrupting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.68,0:04:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm on my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.85,0:04:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then please take care of Goro-chan, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.15,0:04:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.45,0:04:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ran, wasn't her previous cat also named "Goro"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.70,0:04:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mom seems to really like that name, so she used it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.95,0:04:56.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Note: roll around = gorogoro
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.95,0:04:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She used to say it's because cats always roll around, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.96,0:04:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.30,0:05:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why must a great detective like me take care of some freaking cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.97,0:05:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already housebroken, so it's quite easy since all you have to do is make sure it doesn't run outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.93,0:05:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you go ahead and take care of it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.85,0:05:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine if you skip class.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.27,0:05:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have my permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.61,0:05:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Permission, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty busy for the rest of the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:27.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Kirishita, the one who called yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought over the phone we agreed to meet at 9:00 AM, and that it was your wife who was coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.50,0:05:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, my wife is not feeling well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So before I go to work, I've brought it here in her stead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.09,0:05:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My daughter's code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.34,0:05:49.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.85,0:05:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.51,0:05:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.72,0:05:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a message my daughter accidentally sent to my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.89,0:06:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no idea what it says, and my daughter has asked me numerous times to delete it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought it might be an alarming message, and decided to seek your advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.28,0:06:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.82,0:06:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.41,0:06:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was reminded of the novel,\N{\i1}The Deductions of Holmes the Calico Cat{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.58,0:06:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, the series penned by Akagawa Jirou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.50,0:06:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.96,0:06:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the first story of {\i1}Holmes the Calico Cat{\i0}, Holmes was also sitting on someone's shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they say that Russian Blues can be trained to perch upon people's shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.77,0:06:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.60,0:06:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A brat like you should hurry up and get to school already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.90,0:06:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a while ago, you told me not to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.03,0:06:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it does seem true that this message gives out a dangerous vibe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri-san, you think so too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.95,0:06:52.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.45,0:06:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What can be vaguely read is in the second row...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.75,0:06:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Boyfriend"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.83,0:06:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last part in the third row, "plz come with me".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.46,0:07:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That tells us something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.38,0:07:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My daughter is a second year in high school, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.76,0:07:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she recently got a part-time job without telling us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm afraid that maybe some bad guy sweet-talked her into handing over her money...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, my wife fell ill precisely because she's worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.97,0:07:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.31,0:07:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Second year in high school, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.65,0:07:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dangerous age indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.73,0:07:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It so happens that my daughter is also in her second year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.69,0:07:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she's been getting butterflies whenever she thinks of some flashy detective brat
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, didn't I tell you to hurry up and go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.03,0:07:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot something!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.41,0:07:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe this is some sort of code-speak that's popular with teenage girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.25,0:07:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I've also thought of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.63,0:07:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And asked my co-worker's daughter about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.80,0:07:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, what'd she say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.60,0:08:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as she read the message, she let out a smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.35,0:08:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not let your daughter do as she likes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.07,0:08:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.40,0:08:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With an impish smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew this was a dubious message...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.28,0:08:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the time being, please forward this message to my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.21,0:08:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.33,0:08:26.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll contact you soon as I break the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.84,0:08:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.55,0:08:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye then, Goro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.05,0:08:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take care of Uncle, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.73,0:08:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't make heads or tails of it no matter how many times I look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should go wash my face and freshen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did this cat go in the washroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, what a hot potato that landed in my lap...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if only it were as clever as the calico cat in that novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.34,0:09:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.55,0:09:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that cat was sleeping on this towel!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.22,0:09:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.56,0:09:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hell are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are videotapes of Yoko-chan's soap opera!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.27,0:09:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you dare leave as much as a tiny scratch, you'll be sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.74,0:09:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tape for the second episode is missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.95,0:09:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you freaking hid it somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.16,0:09:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, playing with a shoe this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.09,0:09:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this Conan's shoe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.05,0:09:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the hell did you get it from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.30,0:09:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:09:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need two shoes to form a pair!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.51,0:10:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't be of any use if you separate them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep that in your tiny brain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.23,0:10:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.27,0:10:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sneaking up on me and stealing things from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of Holmes, it's looking more like Lupin!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.45,0:10:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This character that looks like an {\i1}o{\i0} with a protruding horn is the small Greek letter {\i1}sigma{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.24,0:10:25.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the crooked {\i1}v{\i0} is the small Greek alphabet {\i1}nu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.58,0:10:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The symbol that resembles a hiragana {\i1}te{\i0} is the small Greek letter {\i1}tau{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.75,0:10:35.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Note: tsukiatte
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.75,0:10:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what appears to be "plz come with me" at the end of the message should read...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.34,0:10:39.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tsukiattau
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.34,0:10:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Please come witauh me".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't even...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.59,0:10:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of the Greek alphabet, it's used in star names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it has something to do with astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.39,0:10:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, I recall an astronomy book was right over here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.48,0:10:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn you, playing pranks again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.95,0:10:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,English-Japanese dictionary?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.82,0:11:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "English-Japanese", it means it translates from English to Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.74,0:11:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this message, the only letter of the English alphabet used is {\i1}W{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.12,0:11:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I force myself into thinking of this W as a Japanese character...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the hiragana {\i1}n{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.05,0:11:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she's playing around with foreign symbols that resemble certain hiragana and katakana?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.31,0:11:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why instead of "tsukiatte" she used "tsukia{\b1}tau{\b0}".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, I guess I'm starting to get the hang of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.86,0:11:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great work, Goro!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.40,0:11:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.69,0:11:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me this cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was trying to tell me all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.25,0:11:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be like in the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:11:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.01,0:11:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is not a toy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.93,0:12:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cats always will be cats after all, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.76,0:12:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, she had purposely substituted foreign characters for hiragana and katakana...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.15,0:12:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's obvious that our young lady wrote this message in a playful way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.65,0:12:19.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I think of it along these lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.90,0:12:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}W{\i0} will be the hiragana {\i1}n{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nu{\i0} will be the katakana {\i1}re{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tau{\i0} will be the hiragana {\i1}te{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.37,0:12:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the {\i1}equal{\i0} sign will be the katakana {\i1}ni{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.70,0:12:33.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the {\i1}postal{\i0} mark must mean the katakana {\i1}te{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.04,0:12:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.67,0:12:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Niteteku"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.76,0:12:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless I decipher the meaning of the {\i1}sigma{\i0} letters which are after {\i1}W{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And before the hiragana {\i1}tsu{\i0}, it seems I can't read it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.47,0:12:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that character does not resemble any hiragana nor katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.39,0:12:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll use a circle to mark the unknown symbols and go from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.90,0:13:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yo n gen en re ka re ni te te ku tsu ki a t te{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So is this some kind of code after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.29,0:13:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.76,0:13:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.85,0:13:35.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, not there again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.65,0:13:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said you can't go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.99,0:13:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already past noon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.74,0:13:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Less than two hours until Yoko-chan's drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.78,0:13:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I don't solve the meaning of this mysterious message before then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.49,0:13:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't relax and watch Yoko-chan's drama, now can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.88,0:14:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.88,0:14:05.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, this little thing also snooped around these tapes earlier, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.26,0:14:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it really be trying to tell me something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only discrepancy that comes to mind is the missing videotape of episode two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.98,0:14:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.06,0:14:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that, this runt slept on my towel in the washroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the fur it shed got on my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.28,0:14:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Dropped" and "missing"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.87,0:14:34.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that the symbols are not only just look-alikes of hiragana and katakana...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.45,0:14:37.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But are also meant to represent corrupted forms of characters on purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:41.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Giving the sense of "Don't you think it's like, cute to use corrupted writings?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the sigma must mean a certain hiragana or katakana but with missing or dropped parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.05,0:14:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, the only character I can think of is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.10,0:14:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hiragana...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.10,0:14:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this plus-minus sign is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.10,0:15:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hiragana...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.44,0:15:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chi{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.65,0:15:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the {\i1}plus-minus{\i0}, {\i1}W{\i0} and {\i1}sigma{\i0} are...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.61,0:15:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chi n no{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.57,0:15:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.20,0:15:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, the right side of the plus-minus sign...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.83,0:15:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I add a stroke there it'll be the hiragana {\i1}chi{\i0}, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.74,0:15:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's on the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll become {\i1}sa{\i0} instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.54,0:15:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this is {\i1}sa{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.54,0:15:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then {\i1}plus-minus{\i0}, {\i1}W{\i0}, and {\i1}sigma{\i0} will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.09,0:15:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sa n no{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that someone's name should go before "-san's"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now my problem is the arrow before the plus-minus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.30,0:15:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I've seen this arrow before, in a certain rich young miss's New Year card.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.44,0:15:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that arrow mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.02,0:15:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.07,0:15:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,(Happy New Year)\N"Akemashite omedeto"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.24,0:15:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrow is the elongation mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.32,0:15:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bar that extends a sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.78,0:15:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the name that goes before the plus-minus...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.24,0:16:01.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should be Satou or Tarou, a name with an -ou ending that sounds like a "long o"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.29,0:16:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll solve it in a jiffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.38,0:16:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.93,0:16:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yo sa n no gen en re ka re{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ni te te ku no tsu ki a t te{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks readable but it's actually not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.77,0:16:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The names that start with {\i1}Yo{\i0} and ends in a long o...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.65,0:16:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would be Yonjou or Youichirou, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.02,0:16:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how I look, they don't fit in at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.95,0:16:35.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.91,0:16:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't play-bite my shoe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.33,0:16:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, this cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was play-biting Conan's shoe earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.79,0:16:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it was only one shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.30,0:16:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I seemed to have said something...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.76,0:16:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.55,0:16:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need two shoes to form a pair!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.84,0:16:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't be of any use if you separate them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Need two to form a pair?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she used two characters to represent a single character!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.90,0:17:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}koto{\i0} meaning "words" and the {\i1}en{\i0} meaning "extend" in the first row...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.56,0:17:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Combine to form {\i1}tan{\i0} or "birth"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.32,0:17:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the two postal marks in the third row form {\i1}gyou{\i0} or "to go".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.49,0:17:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the first hiragana I thought was {\i1}yo{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.99,0:17:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I added the missing stroke back...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.79,0:17:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And paired it with the following iteration mark that looks like the symbol {\i1}>{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.87,0:17:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would actually get the hiragana {\i1}o{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.04,0:17:33.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for the following character, if I pair the L with the mathematic subset symbol resembling a flattened C...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.67,0:17:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall get the hiragana {\i1}to{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.34,0:17:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And pairing the symbol resembling a flattened katakana {\i1}fu{\i0} with the tiny circle makes the katakana {\i1}pu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.64,0:17:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I read the second row using this method...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.98,0:17:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get {\i1}pu re ka i ni{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.56,0:17:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means "buy birthday present"!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.27,0:17:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, if I keep reading...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.52,0:17:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'nn 9onna 9σ buy D@d's |3day prsnt so plz come wiτh me."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:17:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's some surprisingly easy to understand "gal-speak"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:17:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gal-speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.41,0:18:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.12,0:18:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare tell me you're flirting with some young girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.46,0:18:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My client entrusted me with this message.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.92,0:18:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.88,0:18:12.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why the hell are you girls here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.71,0:18:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to school!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.47,0:18:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did go, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.92,0:18:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.89,0:18:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.93,0:18:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then hurry up and prepare dinner at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.85,0:18:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.27,0:18:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.94,0:18:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.15,0:18:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey there, glasses brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.28,0:18:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.74,0:18:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stealing my spotlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite the fact it was the two of us who solved it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.29,0:18:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall give my client a call right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:09.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Note: katsuobushi = dried bonito flakes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My katsuobushi plan was a huge success!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.98,0:19:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I secretly scattered katsuobushi at places where hints could be found...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that the cat would poke around, giving Uncle some hints to solving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.78,0:19:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like my plan worked quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.91,0:19:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this Kirishita-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.57,0:19:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Detective Mouri Kogorou who met with you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.58,0:19:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, have you already...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.08,0:19:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figured out the meaning of my daughter's message?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.83,0:19:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, indeed I have...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.38,0:19:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.80,0:19:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's dangerous, you might fall off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.88,0:19:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was a dangerous message after all!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.22,0:19:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.10,0:19:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your daughter is not dangerous at all, but rather well brought-up...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.06,0:19:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well brought-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.94,0:19:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, idiot, stop pulling!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.90,0:19:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who's pulling at random topics, Mouri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.53,0:19:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.32,0:19:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hurry and tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.86,0:20:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of message was it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.74,0:20:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I promise not to be shocked by the contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.95,0:20:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm ready for the worst scenario!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.82,0:20:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if I give my daughter the third degree about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet my daughter will cough up what she's been secretly doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.29,0:20:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.04,0:20:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri-san, Mouri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.84,0:20:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, in fact I don't understand it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.81,0:20:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.31,0:20:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, I just happened to land myself a huge case earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.56,0:20:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it looks like I'll be tied up with it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.69,0:20:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I actually called you to decline your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.40,0:20:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, since she's a fabulous daughter, I think it's best if you support her and let her be without worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.33,0:20:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you be so sure of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.37,0:20:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like you've met my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.29,0:20:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the Great Detective's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.46,0:20:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Intuition, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.01,0:21:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, say hello to your daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's best that we keep his birthday present a surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.93,0:21:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.77,0:21:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it didn't require my help at all to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.90,0:22:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.07,0:22:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I shall tell Ran to get your dinner prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.12,0:22:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.20,0:22:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.37,0:22:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoko-chan's drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.79,0:22:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not only did I miss it but I forgot to record it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.92,0:23:03.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all because of you fooling around that made me forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.05,0:23:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you even freaking hid my videotape!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.55,0:23:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.93,0:23:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing to my Goro-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.68,0:23:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.39,0:23:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.26,0:23:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you supposed to be in Okinawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was worried about my baby, so I flew back early and plan to finish the rest of my work via phone and fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.32,0:23:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Goro-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.65,0:23:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's say bye-bye to this scary man's place!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.24,0:23:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same Goro, but big difference...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.32,0:23:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the other black-spotted brown Goro you had also attached to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.04,0:23:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very different from a certain dimwit too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.04,0:23:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me "Goro" is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.71,0:23:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Goro" from "Kogorou"?
